Describe wargners classification of ulcers ( 5 mks )
Wagner's classification is a grading system used to assess the severity of diabetic foot ulcers. It helps in guiding treatment and predicting outcomes. The classification is divided into six grades, ranging from 0 to 5:

Grade 0: No open lesions, but there may be pre-ulcerative lesions such as healed ulcers or bony deformities.

Grade 1: Superficial ulcer without penetration to deeper layers. The ulcer is confined to the skin.
Grade 2: Deeper ulcer extending to involve tendon, bone, or joint capsule, but without osteomyelitis (bone infection) or abscess.

Grade 3: Deep ulcer with osteomyelitis or abscess. There is an infection of the bone or a localized collection of pus.

Grade 4: Localized gangrene of a part of the foot, such as toes or the heel.
Grade 5: Extensive gangrene involving the whole foot, necessitating major amputation

